# 8-bit Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU)

An **8-bit Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU)** designed using **Logisim Evolution** to demonstrate the core arithmetic operations and status flag generation used in processor datapaths. The project focuses on modular digital design using basic combinational and sequential logic components.

## Features

* ✅ 8-bit Addition
* ✅ 8-bit Subtraction
* ✅ Multiplexer-based operation selection
* ✅ Result Register for output storage
* ✅ Status Register for flag updates
* ✅ Automatic flag generation

## Supported Operations

| Operation   | Description |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| Addition    | `A + B`     |
| Subtraction | `A - B`     |

## Status Flags

| Flag             | Description                                                |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| **N (Negative)** | Set when the result is negative (MSB = 1)                  |
| **Z (Zero)**     | Set when the result equals zero                            |
| **C (Carry)**    | Set when a carry is generated during arithmetic operations |
| **V (Overflow)** | Set when signed arithmetic overflow occurs                 |

## Components Used

* 8-bit Adder
* 8-bit Subtractor
* Multiplexers (MUX)
* Registers
* Logic Gates
* Splitters

## Project Objectives

* Understand ALU architecture
* Implement arithmetic operations using digital logic
* Generate and update processor status flags
* Practice register-based data storage
* Learn multiplexer-controlled operation selection

